{"id":2447,"date":"2019-04-09T14:07:23","date_gmt":"2019-04-09T19:07:23","guid":{"rendered":"\/?p=2447"},"modified":"2020-11-19T14:11:44","modified_gmt":"2020-11-19T20:11:44","slug":"4-things-to-avoid-while-taking-impressions-at-home","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/blogorigin.wpengine.com\/4-things-to-avoid-while-taking-impressions-at-home\/","title":{"rendered":"4 things to avoid while taking impressions at home"},"content":{"rendered":"<h2><strong>Don\u2019t make these common mistakes taking your at-home dental impressions with the SmileDirectClub impression kit.<\/strong><\/h2>\n<p>We\u2019ve already talked through <a href=\"https:\/\/blogorigin.wpengine.com\/how-make-good-first-impression\">how to take good-quality dental impressions at home<\/a>, but it\u2019s just as important to know what not to do.<\/p>\n<p>Making your impressions is the first step on your <a href=\"https:\/\/blogorigin.wpengine.com\/what-happens-after-you-complete-a-scan-or-impression-kit\/\">journey to a smile you\u2019ll love<\/a>. Since good impressions ensure accurate aligners, and accurate aligners mean happier smiles, we\u2019re here to help make sure you get it right. (But mistakes happen, grinner, which is why we include an extra set that you can use to be more accurate and fix any issues.)<\/p>\n<p>These are the most common mistakes people make while taking their impressions with the SmileDirectClub impression kit and how to fix them.<\/p>\n<h3><strong>1. No gumline present<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p>Each impression must fully capture both your teeth and gums. Use your fingers to firmly and evenly press the tray onto your teeth. Stop once your teeth lightly hit the tray.<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2448\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/04\/bad-dental-impression-No-Gumline.jpg\" alt=\"bad-dental-impression-No-Gumline\" width=\"788\" height=\"525\" srcset=\"https:\/\/blogorigin.wpengine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/04\/bad-dental-impression-No-Gumline.jpg 788w, https:\/\/blogorigin.wpengine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/04\/bad-dental-impression-No-Gumline-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/blogorigin.wpengine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/04\/bad-dental-impression-No-Gumline-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 788px) 100vw, 788px\" \/><\/p>\n<h3><strong>2. Improper putty mixture<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p>The gray and purple putties must be fully mixed until they are one solid color; otherwise, the mixture will not set properly.<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2449\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/04\/bad-dental-impression-improper-Mixture.jpg\" alt=\"bad-dental-impression-improper-Mixture\" width=\"788\" height=\"525\" srcset=\"https:\/\/blogorigin.wpengine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/04\/bad-dental-impression-improper-Mixture.jpg 788w, https:\/\/blogorigin.wpengine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/04\/bad-dental-impression-improper-Mixture-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/blogorigin.wpengine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/04\/bad-dental-impression-improper-Mixture-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 788px) 100vw, 788px\" \/><\/p>\n<h3><strong>3. Double impression<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p>Use your thumbs to gently hold the tray in place and ensure that it does not move while you make your impression.<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2450\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/04\/bad-denta-impressionDouble-Impression.jpg\" alt=\"bad-dental-impression-Double-Impression\" width=\"788\" height=\"525\" srcset=\"https:\/\/blogorigin.wpengine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/04\/bad-denta-impressionDouble-Impression.jpg 788w, https:\/\/blogorigin.wpengine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/04\/bad-denta-impressionDouble-Impression-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/blogorigin.wpengine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/04\/bad-denta-impressionDouble-Impression-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 788px) 100vw, 788px\" \/><\/p>\n<h3><strong>4. Uneven pressure<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p>Use your thumbs to gently push the tray and apply even pressure to both sides. Hold the tray in place to ensure that it does not move while making your impression.<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2451\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/04\/bad-dental-impression-Uneven-Pressure.jpg\" alt=\"bad-dental-impression-Uneven-Pressure\" width=\"788\" height=\"525\" srcset=\"https:\/\/blogorigin.wpengine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/04\/bad-dental-impression-Uneven-Pressure.jpg 788w, https:\/\/blogorigin.wpengine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/04\/bad-dental-impression-Uneven-Pressure-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/blogorigin.wpengine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/04\/bad-dental-impression-Uneven-Pressure-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 788px) 100vw, 788px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Don\u2019t worry about making a bad impression. It could be the worst impression ever created on this green Earth, and we\u2019d still want it. Send all 4 impressions back. Remember, we don\u2019t judge \u2013 we grin.<\/p>\n<p>Ready to join the Club? Order your own impression kit today to get started.<\/p>\n\t<p style=\"text-align: center\">\r\n\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.smiledirectclub.com\/checkout\/?w=impr\" class=\"btn btn--purple\">\r\n\t\t\tOrder Kit\t\t<\/a>\r\n\t<\/p>\r\n\t\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Don\u2019t make these common mistakes.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":20,"featured_media":1699,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[6,869],"tags":[803,570,805,804,569,123,222,568,609,533],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/blogorigin.wpengine.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/2447"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/blogorigin.wpengine.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/blogorigin.wpengine.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/blogorigin.wpengine